text: The Vector Map (VMAP) is a map collection made by The National Geospatial- Intelligence Agency. It is based on the geographic information system. It uses the form of Vector for graphics. It has 2 levels of graphics as of current, Level 0, which uses low-quality images, and is in the public domain. Level 1, which uses medium-quality images, is partly in public domain. Category:Maps
title: Vector Map
